headline: Switch to UPS saved US Postal Service 43% in air transport costs
summary: The U.S. Postal Service is saving a great deal of money with UPS as its prime air cargo vendor instead of FedEx, according to a new inspector general’s report. The post Switch to UPS saved US Postal Service 43% in air transport costs appeared first on FreightWaves.
